author: @dr.walidsoula
text: https://youtu.be/VNfalYYduD4?t=2691 I think you mean, data=dftemp  for Bejaia and data=dftemp2 for Sidi Bel-abbe   # You can show both visualizations at the same time fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 5)) dftemp = df.loc[df["Region"]==0]  sns.countplot(x='month',hue='Classes',data=dftemp,ax=axes[0]) axes[0].set_xlabel("Months") axes[0].set_ylabel('Number of Fire') axes[0].set_title("Fire analysis in Bejaia Region")  dftemp2 = df.loc[df["Region"]==1]  sns.countplot(x='month',hue='Classes',data=dftemp2,ax=axes[1]) axes[1].set_xlabel("Months") axes[1].set_ylabel('Number of Fire') axes[1].set_title("Fire analysis in Sidi Bel-abbes Region")  plt.tight_layout() plt.show()
